<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-22T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-22T03:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3394/265: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-22T17:00:00+09:00">July 22, 1937—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 22—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>221. Department’s 121, July 20, 8 p.m.<note n="66" xml:id="d245fn66">Not printed.</note></p>
                            <p>The Embassy has just been orally informed by the Foreign Office that
                                there is no objection to the visit of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Augusta</hi> and accompanying vessels on the proposed
                                    dates.<note n="67" xml:id="d245fn67">September 20–October 8 to
                                    Yokohama and Kobe.</note> The Japanese Government however
                                requests that these vessels do not enter the Inland Sea <pb facs="0250" n="243" xml:id="pg_243"/> during the month of
                                September. They may do so in October after the Kobe visit.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>